        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 3:29PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 329 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 5 miles northeast of Briscoe to 3 miles
southwest of Wheeler. Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wheeler and Allison.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
